  "text": "Particles enter semiconductor chips from various directions in outer space. We examined Ar-induced CSs depending on incident angles at 0.4 V and 0.8 V at static conditions; (DATA, CLK) = (1, 0) and [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Experiments were carried out for tilt angles of 30, 45 and 60 degrees. Figure 17 shows the experimental setup. Figure 17 (a) presents the tilt angle (θ) of the DUT board. Transistors are tilted as Fig. 17 (b) . The tilt angle affects irradiated fluence into the chip. Effective CS (CS eff ) is calculated from Eq. (2) [CITATION_3] . ",
